[SN]TITLE[SN]
Rio Olympics 2016: Shi Zhiyong wins men's -69kg weightlifting gold

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
China's Shi Zhiyong lifted a combined 352kg to win the men's Olympic -69kg weightlifting title at the Rio Games.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is not supported on this device
Shi, 22, lifted 162kg in the snatch and 198kg in the clean and jerk.
Find out how to get into weightlifting with our special guide.
Daniyar Ismayilov of Turkey led the competition after a 163kg lift in the snatch, but could only manage 188kg in clean and jerk as he was forced to settle for silver with a combined 351kg.
Izzat Artykov of Kyrgyzstan lifted a combined 339kg to win bronze.
